    "summary": "rear security update",
    "details": "Relax-and-Recover is a setup-and-forget Linux bare metal disaster recovery solution. It is easy to set up and requires no maintenance so there is no excuse for not using it.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nRelax-and-Recover (aka ReaR) through 2.7 creates a world-readable initrd when using GRUB_RESCUE=y. This allows local attackers to gain access to system secrets otherwise only readable by root.(CVE-2024-23301)",
